<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">
<B>Guild seniority and loot distribution</B><P><I>***Remember before reading this, no system is perfect.  Officers and raid leaders will try their best, based on these guidelines, to ensure noone is treated unfairly.</I><P>New applicants go to the bottom of the seniority list. Seniority applies to the distribution of items (armor, weapons, etc.) gained on a guild raid. <P>The seniority list operates based on rotation over the course of the various guild raids and events.  If you get an item on a raid you are bumped to the bottom of the list.  You move back up as those above you receive items and as you attend more events.<P>This method allows everyone to obtain equipment upgrades, not just the top one or two chracters in each class.<P>Officers may make exceptions to the seniority list in special circumstances such as epic pieces or the final piece of planar armor.<P>Items that can be used by more than one class will be designated by the raid leader with consultation from the class officers. <P>This list is only reflective of people that raid and are 46+. If you do not attend raids, you are not on the list. <P>Items received will be tracked over the course of the guild's raids and events and the seniority list adjusted based on that information.<P>The current seniority list will be maintained in the guild members forum.<p>[ 24 October 2001: Message edited by: Arocus ]
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
